text: Oum El Bouaghi or Oum el-Bouaghi () is a province (wilaya) of Algeria in the Aures region. The capital is Oum el-Bouaghi, which was named Can Robert (during French occupation), Sidi R'Ghis a few years later, and Oum El Bouaghi before independence. ==Administrative divisions== The province is divided into 12 districts (daïras), which are further divided into 29 communes or municipalities. ===Districts=== # Aïn Babouche # Aïn Beïda # Aïn Fakroun # Aïn Kechra # Aïn M'Lila # Dhalaâ # F'Kirina # Ksar Sbahi # Meskiana # Oum El Bouaghi # Sigus # Souk Naâmane ===Communes=== # Aïn Babouche # Aïn Beïda # Aïn Diss # Aïn Fakroun # Aïn Kercha # Aïn M'lila # Aïn Zitoun # Behir Chergui # Berriche # Bir Chouhada # D'hala (Dhalaâ) # El Amiria # El Belala # El Djazia # El Fedjouz Boughrara Saoudi # El Harmilia # Fkirina (F'Kirina) # Hanchir Toumghani # Ksar Sbahi # Meskiana # Oued Nini # Ouled Gacem # Ouled Hamla # Ouled Zouaï # Oum El Bouaghi # Rahia # Sigus # Souk Naâmane # Zorg ==References== Category:Provinces of Algeria
